<strong>About Craft Coffee:</strong><br />
Craft Coffee sells amazing coffee experiences. We&#39;re building a powerful, global brand by reaching into our customers&#39; everyday rituals, and delivering a disruptively amazing experience. Our first product is a monthly subscription coffee tasting box that currently ships to hundreds of paying subscribers all over the world.</p>
<p>
We&#39;re backed by a global, top-tier group of investors, including Dave McClure&#39;s 500 Startups. We&#39;ve been featured in The Wall Street Journal, WIRED, Fast Company, Esquire, Martha Stewart&#39;s Everyday Food, Bon Appetit, Saveur, Daily Candy, Tasting Table, Serious Eats, Food52 and more.</p>
<p>
<strong>The Position:</strong><br />
We are looking for a highly motivated, tech savvy, social media powerhouse intern to help this fast-growing start-up meet its ambitious goals. Our ideal candidate is very reliable, outgoing, detail-oriented and self-motivated. We&#39;re looking for someone to come in at least 20 hours per week.</p>
<p>
Interns will get to work out of our new office in Williamsburg, Brooklyn. Look forward to being surrounded by good food and hanging on the roof deck this summer.</p>
<p>
<strong>Responsibilities:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
Create original content while maintaining brand voice across all social media platforms (Facebook, Twitter, Google+, etc.)</li>
<li>
Contact publications, editors and bloggers to generate press and follow up on PR leads</li>
<li>
Research other media opportunities, relevant communities, etc.</li>
<li>
Support team with data entry, administrative work and errands as needed.</li>
</ul>
<p>
<strong>Requirements:</strong><br />
<strong>Experience/Education:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
Current undergrad student (pref rising junior or senior) or recent grad</li>
<li>
Coursework in Marketing, Media, English or related field preferred</li>
</ul>
<p>
<strong>Knowledge/Skills:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
Excellent copywriting skills</li>
<li>
Extremely social media savvy</li>
