			<description><![CDATA[<p>
<strong>About Craft Coffee:</strong><br />
Craft Coffee sells amazing coffee experiences. We&#39;re building a powerful, global brand by reaching into our customers&#39; everyday rituals, and delivering a disruptively amazing experience. Our first product is a monthly subscription coffee tasting box that currently ships to hundreds of paying subscribers all over the world.</p>
<p>
We&#39;re backed by a global, top-tier group of investors, including Dave McClure&#39;s 500 Startups. We&#39;ve been featured in The Wall Street Journal, Martha Stewart&#39;s Everyday Food, Bon Appetit, Saveur, Daily Candy, Techcrunch, Tasting Table, Serious Eats, Food52 and more.</p>
<p>
<br />
<strong>The Position:</strong><br />
This intern will work directly with the Founder/CEO to build financial models and work on investor presentations. Ideal candidate would be an outstanding analytical thinker with a passion for creating great customer experiences and driving bottom line success. Experience in analyzing business models, particularly of early-stage companies is a plus. We&#39;re looking for someone who can commit to 15-20 hours per week.</p>
<p>
Interns will get to work at General Assembly, a co-working campus centered on technology, design, and entrepreneurship. This is an amazing opportunity for an aspiring entrepreneur to get a first-hand look at what it takes to be a founder. This internship is unpaid, but the experience is invaluable.</p>
<p>
<br />
<strong>Responsibilities:</strong></p>
